Packet.PacDesc: The configuration request.
Set carrier frequency.
Set bitrate.
Set PacketMode. Configures the radio exchange protocol: 0 - USP, 1 - AX.25 (default)
Set the operating mode. Configures the packet router for different transceiver locations: 0 - onboard, 1 - ground
Set DAC1 calibration. Set the preamp power amplifier calibration value. ATTENTION! This command is technological, its use without control of all transmitted parameters threatens the loss of the SC!
Set DAC2 calibration. Set the preamp power amplifier calibration value. ATTENTION! This command is technological, its use without control of all transmitted parameters threatens the loss of the SC!

Set beacon interval. Sets the period of broadcasting the beacon with the current field values. Data for beacon fields are collected passively starting from the transceiver software download and are updated upon arrival of telemetry from the spacecraft onboard bus devices

Set UniCAN ID. Changes the current address of the device on the UniCAN bus without saving it to non-volatile memory. ATTENTION! This command should be reported with care. Range of valid addresses for the on-board unit: 2-31, the default UHF transceiver address is 0x2
Set SSID. Sets a unique transmitter SSID number ATTENTION! This command is set by the manufacturer

Field.FldDesc: Unique number of the onboard transmitter

Packet.PacDesc: Set the ground SSID. Sets the unique number of the ground-based FCC transceiver. When receiving commands, it is not checked. ATTENTION! This command is set by the manufacturer

Field.FldDesc: Unique number of the ground transmitter.

Packet.PacDesc: Set the CallSign. Sets the unique radio call sign of the onboard transmitter of the ground FCC. All outgoing transmissions will be carried out with this call sign. ATTENTION! This command is set by the manufacturer. The call sign is regulated international agreement. Its setting must be approved by the regulatory authority

Set EarthCallSign. Sets the unique number of the ground-based FCC transmitter. When receiving commands, the following commands will be executed: only those that came from this station. ATTENTION! This command is set by the manufacturer.

Field.FldDesc: Radio callsign of the ground control transmitter

Packet.PacDesc: Activate the bridge mode. Sets the mode of operation of the packet router from the radio channel to the on-Board bus: 0 - packet forwarding is prohibited, 1 - packets are being forwarded. ATTENTION! This command is set by the manufacturer.

Field.FldDesc: Activate bridge mode with onboard network

Packet.PacDesc: Save settings to ROM. Save all current settings to the nonvolatile memory of the transceiver ATTENTION! The command can lead to the loss of the SC! Check that the current settings are correct with the command request_All Configuration and make sure that stable communication with the SC is possible. Saved settings will work after each next reboot
Reset by timer. Reset the transceiver after the specified time in seconds. For immediate reboot parameter 0 is passed. ATTENTION! Communication will be unavailable for a few seconds after reboot
Cancel reset timer. Set the restart timer with a value equal to 5 days. The same timer is used as in the command Reset
Set time. Sets the current onboard time, using the Unixtime-32 format. ATTENTION! Onboard time in UTC format. Setting an incorrect time can lead to unpredictable behavior of the SC
UHF telemetry request.
UHF beacon request.

Beacon. The main packet of the periodic beacon, the period is set by the set_BeaconInterval command. Send with extendedBeacon packet. Beacon transmission is activated automatically after loading the transceiver, after expiration of the BeaconDelay timer and subject subject to the permission of the beacon BeaconEnable. Beacon data data is collected in passive mode as telemetry is received from onboard devices

Extended beacon. Extended packet of periodic beacon, transmitted automatically after the main Beacon packet Beacon transmission is activated automatically after loading the transceiver, after expiration of the BeaconDelay timer and subject subject to the permission of the beacon BeaconEnable. Beacon data data is collected in passive mode as telemetry is received from onboard devices

Packet.PacDesc: Set Beacon startup delay. Sets the time interval for prohibiting automatic transmission of the beacon. The ban is performed once each time the transceiver is turned on and restarted, after the specified time, automatic transmission is allowed

Set current beacon delay. Set the current countdown timer to disable automatic beacon transmission. Can be used to extend or reset the base interval set by BeaconStartupDelay parameter. Used by PSS when connecting an external charger
Request for onboard time. Time in Unixtime-32 format
